    <h3>PDF Embed</h3>
    <p>Display a PDF inline with a download link fallback.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="PDF with download fallback">{{ pdfObjectCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Nested Fallback Chain</h3>
    <p><code>&lt;object&gt;</code> elements can be nested to create a fallback chain. The browser tries each in order, stopping at the first one it can render.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Nested fallback chain">{{ fallbackChainCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>The Fallback Content Pattern</h2>
    <p>Unlike void elements such as <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> and <a href="/docs/elements/native/embed/"><code>&lt;embed&gt;</code></a>, <code>&lt;object&gt;</code> supports fallback content between its tags. This content is rendered when:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The resource specified by <code>data</code> cannot be loaded</li>
      <li>The browser does not support the resource's MIME type</li>
      <li>The <code>type</code> attribute specifies an unsupported format</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This makes <code>&lt;object&gt;</code> useful for progressive enhancement scenarios where you want a graceful degradation path.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data</code></td>
          <td>URL of the resource to embed. Required for most use cases.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>type</code></td>
          <td>MIME type of the resource (e.g., <code>image/svg+xml</code>, <code>application/pdf</code>). Helps the browser decide how to handle the content.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>width</code></td>
          <td>Display width of the object in pixels.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>height</code></td>
          <td>Display height of the object in pixels.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>name</code></td>
          <td>Name for the embedded browsing context (used with forms and links targeting this object).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>form</code></td>
          <td>Associates the object with a <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> element by ID.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>This element also supports <a href="/docs/elements/native/states/">global attributes</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <p>Because <code>&lt;object&gt;</code> embeds opaque external content, accessibility depends on providing good fallback content and ARIA attributes.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Accessible object with fallback text">{{ accessibleObjectCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Best Practices</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Always provide meaningful fallback content between the <code>&lt;object&gt;</code> tags</li>
      <li>Add <code>role="img"</code> and <code>aria-label</code> when embedding images or charts</li>
      <li>Fallback content should convey the same information as the embedded resource</li>
      <li>Include download links in fallback content so users can still access the resource</li>
      <li>Prefer native elements (<code>&lt;img&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;video&gt;</code>) which have built-in accessibility semantics</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/embed/"><code>&lt;embed&gt;</code></a> - Void element for embedding; no fallback content support</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/iframe/"><code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code></a> - For embedding HTML documents with full security controls</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/img/"><code>&lt;img&gt;</code></a> - For images (raster and external SVG); use <code>alt</code> text instead of fallback content</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/video/"><code>&lt;video&gt;</code></a> - For video with native controls, captions, and multiple sources</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/audio/"><code>&lt;audio&gt;</code></a> - For audio with native controls and multiple sources</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/svg/"><code>&lt;svg&gt;</code></a> - For inline vector graphics with full CSS and DOM control</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
